Do not include rosidl_typesupport_{c,cpp} in rmw impl typesupport list (#348)

Signed-off-by: Christophe Bedard <bedard.christophe@gmail.com>

Replace hero section background with enhanced particle system

Hero Section Changes:
- Removed purple gradient background effects (::before pseudo-element)
- Removed static radial gradients and pulse animation
- Simplified to clean dark background for better particle visibility

Enhanced Particle System:
- Increased particle frequency (100ms instead of 150ms)
- Larger particle sizes (3-11px instead of 2-8px)
- Higher opacity range (0.3-1.2 instead of 0.2-1.0)
- Longer particle lifespan (9000ms instead of 8000ms)
- More frequent colored particles (120ms instead of 200ms)

New Hero-Specific Particles:
- Added multi-directional particle spawning (bottom, left, right, top)
- Created 4 new animation types: floatUp, floatDown, floatRight, floatLeft
- Particles spawn from all screen edges with random trajectories
- Enhanced glow effects and rotation animations

Ambient Floating Particles:
- Added slow-moving ambient particles that float in place
- Created smooth scaling and position animations
- Longer duration ambient effects (18 seconds)
- Gentle pulsing opacity for atmospheric effect

Overall Effect:
- Hero section now has same dynamic particle system as rest of site

issue.title: feat: Implement three-tier search index system with unified search
issue.body:
## Summary

This PR implements a comprehensive three-tier search index architecture for DollhouseMCP, enabling efficient searching across local portfolio, GitHub portfolio, and collection sources with performance optimizations and unified search capabilities.

## Problem Solved

The previous implementation had several critical issues:
1. **submit_content** couldn't find elements by metadata name (only filename)
2. **search_collection** wasn't searching the local portfolio
3. No efficient way to search across all content sources
4. Collection API calls were slow for large datasets
5. **portfolio_status** wasn't counting all element types

## Solution Architecture

### Three-Tier Index System
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         UnifiedIndexManager             │
├─────────────┬──────────────┬────────────┤
│   Local     │   GitHub     │ Collection │
│   Index     │   Index      │   Index    │
├─────────────┼──────────────┼────────────┤
│ Portfolio   │ GitHub       │ Collection │
│ IndexMgr    │ Portfolio    │ IndexCache │
│ (existing)  │ Indexer      │   (new)    │
└─────────────┴──────────────┴────────────┘
```

## Major Features Implemented

### 1. 🔍 Unified Search Capabilities
- **New `search_all` MCP Tool**: Search across all three sources simultaneously
  - Source filtering (local, github, collection)
  - Pagination support
  - Multiple sort options
  - Element type filtering
- **Enhanced `submit_content`**: Pre-submission duplicate detection with version comparison
- **Rich Formatting**: Source icons and visual indicators for better UX

### 2. ⚡ Performance Optimizations
- **LRU Cache**: Memory-aware caching with O(1) operations
  - Configurable memory limits (default 50MB)
  - TTL-based expiration
  - Automatic cleanup on memory pressure

pull_request.title: Fix bubble horizontal velocity synchronization with obstacles using minimal hybrid approach
pull_request.body:
## Problem

Bubbles and obstacles were using different movement systems that could cause synchronization issues. The original issue was that bubbles weren't moving horizontally at the same speed as obstacles, making the forward movement simulation effect inconsistent.

- **Bubbles**: Used physics velocity `setVelocityX(-150)` and `setVelocityY()` managed by Phaser's physics engine
- **Obstacles**: Used manual position updates `x += -150 * delta/1000` in the update loop

## Solution

Implemented a **minimal hybrid approach** that only changes the horizontal movement system:

```javascript
// Horizontal movement: Manual (synchronized with obstacles)
bubble.moveSpeedX = GAME_CONFIG.BUBBLES.SPEED_X; // -150 pixels/second
bubble.x += bubble.moveSpeedX * this.game.loop.delta / 1000;

// Vertical movement: Physics-based (natural falling preserved)
bubble.body.setVelocityY(Phaser.Math.Between(20, 80));
```

## Benefits

- **Perfect horizontal synchronization**: Both bubbles and obstacles move at exactly -150 pixels/second using the same manual timing mechanism
- **Natural falling physics preserved**: Bubbles still fall naturally using Phaser's physics engine for Y movement
- **Minimal changes**: Only modified the horizontal movement system, keeping existing physics behavior for vertical movement
- **Frame-rate independent**: Consistent behavior across different devices and frame rates

The solution provides the exact velocity matching requested while maintaining the natural physics-based falling behavior and minimizing changes to the existing system.

![Bubble Movement Fix](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/90e9b802-35ef-4c1e-bc1d-11aa40ab6528)

**Insights into your code**:  Ask any questions on your codebase within the pull request 

**Chat about your code** : Chat with the bot around your code. The more you chat, the smarter it gets.

**Issue Validation**:  Validates the PR against the linked issues and identifies other related issues
